==Style of play==
McCall was a [[Midfielder#"Box-to-box" midfielders|box-to-box midfielder]] characterised by his tireless running,<ref name="telegraph"/> tackling and also weighing in with an average of one goal every 11 games.<ref name="stats">{{cite web
|url=http://www.soccerbase.com/players_details.sd?playerid=4982
|title=Stuart McCall
|accessdate=2008-01-14
|publisher=The Racing Post}}</ref> Despite his position in the middle of the park he was rarely suspended and was sent off just once in his career&mdash;in the final minute of a 2&ndash;0 defeat to [[Charlton Athletic F.C.|Charlton Athletic]] on 4 November 2000.<ref>{{cite news
|first=John
|last=Ley
|url=http://www.telegraph.co.uk/sport/main.jhtml?xml=/sport/2000/11/06/sfncha06.xml
|title=Toothless Bradford suffer pain
|date=[[2000-11-07]]
|accessdate=2008-01-14
|publisher=The Daily Telegraph}}</ref><ref name="stats"/> He also had a never-say-die attitude proven by a number of key late goals including his equaliser which sent the [[1989 FA Cup Final]] into extra-time,<ref name="telegraph"/> and a 93rd minute equaliser against [[Tottenham Hotspur F.C.|Tottenham Hotspur]] during Bradford's difficult start to their Premier League campaign in the [[FA Premier League 1999-2000|1999&ndash;2000]] season.<ref>{{cite news
|first=Richard
|last=Sutcliffe
|url=http://archive.thetelegraphandargus.co.uk/1999/9/13/161694.html
|title=Supermac to the rescue!
|date=[[1999-09-13]]
|accessdate=2008-01-14
|publisher=Telegraph & Argus}}</ref> He was a passionate player whose strong desire to win even ran to reserve games.<ref>{{cite news
|first=Peter
|last=Gardner
|url=http://www.telegraph.co.uk/sport/main.jhtml?xml=/sport/2003/12/01/sfgshe01.xml
|title=McCall defying time
|date=[[2003-11-30]]
|accessdate=2008-01-14
|publisher=The Daily Telegraph}}</ref> Even in his final years of his career he was described as a player with "plenty of drive and ambition" by manager [[Neil Warnock]].<ref>{{cite news
|url=http://www.thesun.co.uk/sol/homepage/sport/football/article178864.ece
|title=Weekend soccer snippets
|date=[[2002-09-14]]
|accessdate=2008-01-16
|publisher=The Sun}}</ref>

